snippet.textDisplay: What about gaining the capital from oil extraction to invest in development of more efficient energy technology, even based on fossil fuel? Before we get to renewable from now we should get sustainable on the way, which on its own requires breakthroughs. Exchange of competent people between the corporations and more accurate extraction process are perhaps one step ahead of just banning oil extraction (which we all rely on). There are no single step, simple solutions to such complex problems. Legislation, education and cash flow are our only parameters, which we can reinvent the future energy economy with.
